				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A method I've used for timed events is to use a small structure of addresses with counters. Every NMI they are all checked: Any counters that are set are decremented and any that hit zero are called (the addresses part). The callback procedure that is called can then do it's thing, and reset it's timer (or not). This way, you can setup a timed events and not have to check their timers in your main logic once they are setup.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

