					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I use this to accomplish it:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #&gt;(return-1)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; set return address<br />pha<br />lda #&lt;(return-1)<br />pha<br /><br />lda vectorHI,y<br />pha<br />lda vectorLO,y<br />pha<br /><br />rts&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; jump<br /><br />return:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; return here<br /></div><br /><br />I have a 'module' for this. I like to set things up and treat them as generic system functions, so my main code would access this through: <br /><br />add_vector (send address, default frames) (This will adjust address so it works with rts)<br />reset_vectors (clear all)<br />The routine that is called needs to do this:<br />set_frame_counter ( send new frames to wait, zero = clear this callback)<br /><br />Actually, if the routine in question does not call set_frame_counter it will default to resetting to the last counter.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

